,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus 1759: 1325) Swartz (1803: 274)" authorityName="Swartz" authorityPageNumber="274" authorityYear="1803" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus 1759:" baseAuthorityPageNumber="1325" baseAuthorityYear="1325" box="[646,1215,1624,1647]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reticulatum">
<emphasis box="[646,805,1624,1646]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">M. reticulatum (</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[805,1012,1624,1646]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refId="ref6795" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1759) Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. reformata. Editio 10. Salvius, Stockholm, 1384 pp." type="book" year="1759">Linnaeus 1759: 1325</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Swartz, O." box="[1026,1215,1625,1647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="273 - 312" refId="ref7981" refString="Swartz, O. (1803) Observationes botanicae Genera et Species Filicum illustrantes. Journal fur die Botanik 1801 (2): 273 - 312." type="journal article" year="1803">Swartz (1803: 274)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mettenius 1859: 22) Pichi Sermolli (1968: 180)" authorityName="Pichi Sermolli" authorityPageNumber="180" authorityYear="1968" baseAuthorityName="Mettenius" baseAuthorityPageNumber="22" baseAuthorityYear="1859" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="membranaceum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">M. membranaceum (</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mettenius, G." box="[197,383,1660,1683]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refId="ref6919" refString="Mettenius, G. (1859) Filices Lechlerianae, 2. Lipsiae: Leopold Voss, 38 pp." type="book" year="1859">Mettenius 1859: 22</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Pichi Sermolli, R. E. G." box="[395,649,1660,1683]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 319" refId="ref7041" refString="Pichi Sermolli, R. E. G. (1968) Fragmenta Pteridologiae - I. Webbia 23 (1): 1 - 319. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00837792.1968.10669884" type="journal article" year="1968">Pichi Sermolli (1968: 180)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of buds in axils of pinnae and having triangular-lanceolate pinnae. It differs from these species mainly by the presence of the dense indument of scales and trichomes on the abaxial surface of the lamina, appressed trichomes on the main veins and costae, asymmetric pinna bases, round sori, and glands on the sporangia.
</paragraph>
